(126, 1, '2012-06-25 21:10:11', '2012-06-26 01:10:11', 'About us\r\n<h3>Carnatic Music</h3>\r\n\r\nCarnatic music is the classical music of southern india which comprises of 4 states. Tamilnadu, AndraPradesh, Karnataka and Kerala. It is based on the 72 nomenclature system of ragas. The 72 ragas are called Janaka or parent Ragas. The ragas derived from these parent ragas are called Janya ragas or derived ragas.The basic elements of sruti (the relative musical pitch), swara (the musical sound of a single note), raga (the mode or melodic formula), and Tala (the rhythmic cycles) form the foundation of improvisation and composition in Carnatic music. Although improvisation plays an important role, Carnatic music is mainly sung through compositions, especially the kriti (or keertanams).The main emphasis in Carnatic music is on vocal music; most compositions are written to be sung, and even when played on instruments, they are meant to be performed in the singing style.Add the glossary from ragamalika.', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '82-revision-4', '', '', '2012-06-25 21:10:11', '2012-06-26 01:10:11', '', 82, 'http://bramkaslp01/ragamalika/82-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
